SENATE BILL DRS45254-BAxf-11
Short Title: Horse Race Wagering Modifications. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Moffitt, Hanig, and McInnis (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO AUTHORIZE CERTAIN PARI-MUTUEL WAGERING AND HORSE RACING.
3 Whereas, the General Assembly finds that horse racing has the potential to create
4 thousands of jobs for North Carolina citizens in agricultural, retail, hospitality, tourism,
5 veterinarian, and other sectors of the economy; and
6 Whereas, authorized and regulated pari-mutuel wagering will help foster and grow
7 the North Carolina equine industry; and
8 Whereas, experiences in other states have demonstrated the benefits of regulated
9 horse racing and pari-mutuel wagering; Now, therefore,
10 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
11 SECTION 1. Article 10 of Chapter 18C of the General Statutes reads as rewritten:
12 "Article 10.
13 "Pari-Mutuel Wagering.
14 "§ 18C-1000. (Reserved)
15 "§ 18C-1001. Definitions.
16 As used in this Article, the following definitions apply:
17 (1) Adjusted gross revenue. – The total of all moneys paid to a pari-mutuel
18 wagering licensee as pari-mutuel wagers minus federal excise taxes and minus
19 the total amount paid out to winning bettors, including the cash value of
20 merchandise awarded as winnings and the cash value of any incentives
21 provided to bettors.
22 (1a) Advance deposit account wager or advance deposit account wagering. – A
23 pari-mutuel wager on horse races in accordance with 15 U.S.C. Chapter 57
24 and the rules adopted by the Commission.A form of pari-mutuel wagering
25 made in accordance with 15 U.S.C. §§ 3001-3007 and exclusively on an ADW
26 wagering platform, whereby an individual may establish an account with a
27 person or entity licensed by the Commission and may place a pari-mutuel
28 wager through that account as permitted by law.
29 (2) ADW licensee. – Any person or entity licensed by the Commission in
30 accordance with this Article.Any person, including a legacy track operator and
31 a startup track operator, licensed by the Commission to conduct advance
32 deposit account wagering and accept deposits and wagers, issue a receipt or
33 other confirmation to the account holder evidencing such deposits and wagers,
34 and transfer credits and debits to and from accounts; provided, however, a
35 person with an ADW license that is not also a legacy track operator or a startup
