35 wagering.
36 (5) Simulcast facility. – Any facility approved by the Commission to simulcast
37 horse racing and conduct pari-mutuel wagering through an ADW
38 licensee.controlled by a legacy track operator or startup track operator that
39 offers pari-mutuel wagering on horse races provided through simulcasting.
40 (6) Standardbred. – A horse that is driven by a driver and registered with the
41 United States Trotting Association.
42 (6a) Standardbred track. – A horse track in this State that conducts horse races for
43 at least standardbred horses but not thoroughbred horses.
44 (7) Startup track. – An actual or proposed horse track in this State that is not a
45 legacy track and that hosts or intends to host horse races pursuant to this
46 Article.
