31 "§ 18C-1004. Startup track licenses.
32 (a) Applications for startup track licenses will be evaluated on a comparative basis. One
33 startup track license will be for a thoroughbred track, and it shall be issued before the second
34 startup track license, which shall be for a standardbred horse track. Because this procurement
35 process is comparative, the Commission is delegated the discretion to choose which two
36 applicants best satisfy the criteria and purposes of this Article.
37 (1) The first procurement process for a startup track license will be for a
38 thoroughbred track.
39 a. The Commission will accept applications pursuant to this procurement
40 process on a date certain that is not less than three months nor more
41 than six months after the Commission awards at least one legacy track
42 license.
43 b. The Commission shall not award a startup track license for a
44 thoroughbred track to any applicant that does not commit to (i) making
45 a minimum investment of three hundred fifty million dollars
46 ($350,000,000) in this State to develop or enhance the startup track
47 and (ii) offer to provide at least 50 live race days within three years of
48 being issued the startup track license for the thoroughbred track.
49 c. If the Commission determines that none of the applications qualify for
50 a startup track license for a thoroughbred track, the Commission shall
51 not award a license and commence another procurement process for
